episodes.title: A message from Zealot
episodes.description: So long, and thanks for all the cults.

episodes.title: Zealot 47: Donald Trump with Matt Bevan
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Matt Bevan about a guy who shares a load of characteristics with cult leaders, if he could only just get organised: Donald Trump.

episodes.title: Zealot 46: Keith Ham with Josh Dean
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Josh Dean about a guy who did more damage to the Hare Krishna reputation than repetitive airport chanting: Keith Ham.

episodes.title: Zealot 45: Doc Antle with Paul Verhoeven
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Paul Verhoeven about a man who made everyone who watched Tiger King say hmmmm: Doc Antle.

episodes.title: Zealot 44: Lawrence Ray with Rhys Nicholson
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Rhys Nicholson about a man who made a college dorm look even more like a cult than usual: Lawrence Ray.

episodes.title: Zealot 43: The Buddhafield with Marieke Hardy
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Marieke Hardy about a cult led by a man skilled in the arts of manipulation, push-ups, and Speedo-wearing: The Buddhafield.

episodes.title: Zealot 42: Camp David with Cal Wilson
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Cal Wilson about a Kiwi cult that she visited as a child, remembering the headscarves and gardening, but not the huge cache of weapons: Camp David.

episodes.title: Zealot 40: Gwen Shamblin with Yvie Jones
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Yvie Jones about a big-haired lady who’ll tell you Jesus wants you to be skinny and fat people go to hell: Gwen Shamblin.

episodes.title: Zealot 39: The Manson Family with Lauren Bonner
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Lauren Bonner about a guy who took a short break from being a prison inmate to develop his skills as a songwriter and cult leader: Charles Manson.

episodes.title: Zealot 38: Jared Leto with Rose Callaghan
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Rose Callaghan about an actor whose most convincing roles are as a rock star and a cult leader: Jared Leto.

episodes.title: Zealot 37: Teal Swan with Brianna Williams
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Brianna Williams about a woman who has made sure you’ll find her if you Google how to kill yourself: Teal Swan.

episodes.title: Zealot 36: Westboro Baptist Church with Alex Jae
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Alex Jae about a family that hates you, pancakes and nerds, but LOVES bedroom murals and knock-off Ed Hardy: Westboro Baptist Church.

episodes.title: Zealot 35: Aleister Crowley with Gary Smith
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Gary Smith about a clever trust fund brat with an unhygienic attitude towards canapés: Aleister Crowley.

episodes.title: Zealot 34: Grace Road Church with Rob Stott
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Rob Stott about a cult that slaps the demons out of you and serves pizza afterwards: Grace Road Church.

episodes.title: Zealot 33: Oneida with Lucas Brown
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Lucas Brown about a cult that loved communism, forks and fornicating: The Oneida Community.

episodes.title: Zealot 32: Universal Medicine with Alison Piotrowski
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Alison Piotrowski about a cult that loves the twin themes of reincarnation and boobs: Universal Medicine.

episodes.title: Zealot 31: DeVernon LeGrand with Jeremy Davidson
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Jeremy Davidson about a murderous cult leader whose only assets were fake nuns and sartorial style : DeVernon LeGrand.

episodes.title: Zealot 30: John De Ruiter with Natalie Norman LIVE at Toronto True Crime Film Festival
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Natalie Norman live at the Toronto True Crime Film Festival about a guy who balances on the twin pillars of okayness and staring: John De Ruiter.

episodes.title: Zealot 29: The Source Family with Simone Holtznagel

episodes.title: Zealot 28: R Kelly with Chris Deal
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Chris Deal about a guy accused of both running a sex cult and dropping killer jams: R Kelly.

episodes.title: Zealot 27: NXIVM with Brock Wilbur
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Brock Wilbur about a cult-slash-multi-level-marketing organisation inspired by Scientology, Amway, and deep misogyny: NXIVM.

episodes.title: Zealot 26: The Little Pebble with Dan Ilic
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Dan Ilic about a cult led by a guy who calls himself “The Little Pebble” but who others call “a convicted paedophile”: The Order of St Charbel.

episodes.title: Zealot 25: Full Circle with Alex Monnig

episodes.title: Zealot 24: Synanon with Myf Warhurst

episodes.title: Zealot 23: Twelve Tribes with Bec Charlwood

episodes.title: Zealot 21: Universe People with Patrick Lenton

episodes.title: Zealot 20: Tony Alamo with Adam Richard

episodes.title: Zealot 19: House of David with Colin Delaney

episodes.title: Zealot 18: FLDS with Jan Fran

episodes.title: Zealot 17: The Family with Shelley Stocken

episodes.title: Zealot 16: Unarius with Mat Whitehead

episodes.title: Zealot 15 Roch Theriault with Dan Barrett

episodes.title: Zealot 14 Aggressive Christianity Missions Training Corps with Michael Beveridge

episodes.title: Zealot 12: Sherry Shriner with Dan Debuf

episodes.title: Zealot 11: Aum Shinrikyo with Andrew P Street
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Andrew P Street about the cult that ruined train travel and hair tea for everyone: Aum Shinrikyo.

episodes.title: Zealot 10: Branch Davidians with Greg Morrow
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Greg Morrow about the cult that was good news for fire but bad news for Vernons: The Branch Davidians.

episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Lorin Pickup about the cult that started with a Brylcreem messiah and ended with one of the biggest mass suicides of all time: Jonestown.

episodes.title: Zealot 8: Heaven's Gate with Russ Tainton
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Russ Tainton about the cult that stopped a sneaker line and abandoned its testes: Heaven's Gate.

episodes.title: Zealot 7: Colonia Dignidad with Nadine Von Cohen
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Nadine Von Cohen about an evil Chilean Nazi torture cult so heinous they made a bad movie about it: Colonia Dignidad

episodes.title: Zealot 6: The Moonies with Kerri Sackville
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Kerri Sackville about the cult well known for mass weddings and less well known for disgusting sex handkerchiefs: The Moonies.

episodes.title: Zealot 5: Rajneeshees with Rachael Mogan McIntosh
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Rachael Mogan McIntosh about the cult that inspired luxury car ownership, salad bar terrorism, and tough titties: The Rajneeshees.

episodes.title: Zealot 4: Hollow Earth with Eddie Sharp
episodes.description: Do we live inside the Earth or is it full of racists and waterfalls? Are they the same thing? Jo Thornely wonders with Eddie Sharp

episodes.title: Zealot 3: Raelians with Katie Jamieson
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Katie Jamieson about the go-to cult for man-buns and active wear: The Raelians

episodes.title: Zealot 2: Children of God with Tristan Lutze
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Tristan Lutze about Children of God, a cult responsible for the world's creepiest boob comics.

episodes.title: Zealot 1: Scientology with Jacqui Kassulke
episodes.description: Jo Thornely talks to Jacqui Kassulke about everybody's favourite cult for short people and aliens: Scientology,
